article.description: Janeth Arcain scored 15 of her season-high 23 points in the second half as the Houston Comets beat the Utah Starzz 78-67 on Wednesday night for their eighth win a row.
article.headline: Starzz miss suspended Dydek in loss to Comets
article.linkText: Arcain's 23 points pace Comets to eighth straight win
article.story:
SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- Janeth Arcain scored 15 of her season-high 23 points in the second half as the Houston Comets beat the Utah Starzz 78-67 on Wednesday night for their eighth win a row. "In the second half, I got tough on defense and got confidence to make my shot,'' Arcain said. Sheryl Swoopes added 22 points and Tina Thompson 20 as the Comets shot 62 percent in the second half to help the Comets (13-3) erase a seven-point halftime deficit. Arcain was the key to the Comets' surge as the Starzz went to a triangle-and two defense to stop Swoopes and Thompson. "She got in the middle of that defense and made shot after shot. It was her best half of the season,'' Houston coach Van Chancellor said. Marie Ferdinand led Utah (9-5) with 16 points, and Adrienne Goodson had 15 but the Starzz shot just 29 percent from the field in the second half. The Starzz have lost just twice in their last seven games, both to Houston. The Starzz were without center Margo Dydek, who was suspended one game for elbowing Cleveland center Ann Wauters in the head in the first half of Utah's 79-62 victory over the Rockers on Sunday. "Would Dydek have made a difference? Absolutely,'' Chancellor said. "I was happy not to have to deal with her tonight.'' The Comets blocked a franchise-record 11 shots, led by Michelle Snow's three, as Houston outscored Utah 24-6 to start the second half. "We've always been a great defensive team and we finally showed that in the second half,'' Chancellor said. Trailing 40-33 at the half, Arcain scored seven points in a 11-2 run that gave Houston the lead. Without 7-foot-2 Dydek patrolling the lane, Swoopes and Arcain drove to the basket constantly in the second half. The Starzz said the impact of not having Dydek was clear. "It was huge,'' Jennifer Azzi said. "She often is the difference.'' Arcain's layup with 11:24 remaining capped a 13-0 surge that made it 57-46 for Houston. "We got more aggressive during that stretch. It was time we put the pressure on them,'' said Swoopes, who played with considerable pain in her surgically repaired left knee. With the Comets' defensive pressure and blocked shots, Utah could never get within striking distance the rest of the way.

Game notes
Swoopes played with a brace on her surgically repaired left knee for first time this season. ... Starzz players all had Dydek's No. 12 written on their shoulders or headbands. ... Utah activated forward Danielle Cockrum and placed guard LaNeisha Caufield on the injured list with what was called a left lower extremity stress fracture.
